        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 2:18AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>Relative humidity values between 20 and 25 percent will combine
with wind gusts of 10 to 15 mph and dry fuels is expected this
afternoon. This will result in an increased fire danger.

People are urged to avoid outdoor burning. If you must burn, use
extreme caution since fires can grow quickly and become dangerous
in these conditions. Ensure that fire suppression equipment is
readily available. Properly extinguish and dispose of any smoking
materials.

The North Carolina Forest Service has issued a statewide ban on
all open burning until further notice, and all burning permits
have been cancelled. Residents with questions can contact their
NC Forest Service county ranger or their county fire marshal's
office.
</description>
